The reason these letters exist is because Unicode has a policy of 1-to-1 round trip encoding compatibility with older character sets, and Yugoslavia (keep in mind Unicode came out in 1991) used to have an 8-bit character set (YUSCII) that included these digraph letters. Iâ€™m not sure why so many commentators are focused on Hungarian.





